About 16.4% of South Africans are smokers according to the latest national statistics in South African National Health and Nutrition Examination survey in 2012. There are many health risks when it comes to smoking cigarettes, however there are still so many people who smoke. People smoke cigarettes and are aware of the health risks, however choosing to quit smoking cigarettes can be very difficult just like trying to quit any addiction. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>If you are a smoker, here are some reasons to consider quitting smoking: 1. Health You will become a much healthier person. According to Lung.org When a smoker quits smoking, your body begins to repair the damage caused by smoking. 2. MoneyYou will be able to save a lot more money or use the money spent buying cigarettes on something else. In South Africa a box of cigarettes costs between R35-R45. If you calculate the money spent buying one box of cigarettes a week, a smoker can spend up to R1820 - R2340 a year on cigarettes. 3. Smoking can affect your sex life According to Health.com, smoking can affect the blood flow circulation to your genitals resulting in arousal to be more difficult than non-smokers. 4. You can sleep better Going through nicotine (the toxics in a cigarette) withdrawal can contribute to disturbed sleep, According to Health.com. 5. Smoking speeds up aging process If you're a smoker for more than 10 years, you probably look older than what you're actually supposed to look. According to Health.com Smoking narrows your skins blood vessels and damages the tissues that give the skin its strength and elasticity.